What [`strlen` function](https://linux.die.net/man/3/strlen) returns is `size_t`,
so you should use it to store its return value.

    char * f_sparce_arg(char words[]){
        size_t words_length; /* use proper type */
        words_length = strlen(words);
    
        printf(&quot;%zu&quot;,words_length); /* the format to print size_t value is %zu */
        return &quot;&quot;;
    }

Unfortunately, `%zu` format is not supported in some compilers or libraries.
Another way is, if the string won&#39;t be so long, to cast the return value to `int`.

    char * f_sparce_arg(char words[]){
        int words_length;
        words_length = (int)strlen(words); /* explicitly cast the result to avoid warnings */
    
        printf(&quot;%d&quot;,words_length);
        return &quot;&quot;;
    }

